d2449fa84bcf2ab6010e56b43a8c95b3.description: VINEYARD OFFSHORE, LLC THREE-DAY ADVANCED NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.2(c)(2)(B) of the California Public Utilities Commissions (CPUC or Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, Vineyard Offshore, LLC (Vineyard Offshore) hereby gives advanced notice of two scheduled ex parte meetings. The first meeting is scheduled for August 19, 2024, at 12:30 p.m. The meeting will be with Karolina Maslanka, advisor to President Alice Busching Reynolds, and with Suzanne Thompson and Maria Sotero, advisors to Commissioner John Reynolds. The second meeting is scheduled for August 23, 2024, at 9:30 a.m. The meeting will be with Jason Symonds, advisor to Commissioner Karen Douglas. The purpose of each meeting is to discuss the Proposed Decision determining need for centralized procurement of long lead-time resources, and in particular, the provisions involving offshore wind development in California. Both meetings will take place via WebEx, and each is expected to last thirty minutes. Participants representing Vineyard Offshore at both meetings are expected to include Rick Umoff, Director of Government Affairs, West Coast for Vineyard Offshore; Carrie Hitt, Senior Director, Grid and Transmission Policy for Vineyard Offshore; Michael Hagerty, Principal, The Brattle Group; Maureen Gorsen, Partner at Sidley Austin LLP; and Kenneth Irvin, Partner at Sidley Austin LLP.

f2071a2cfbca4d0f023ea0f4dfe17914.description: NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATIONOF INVENERGY, LLC. Pursuant to Rule 8.4(a) of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission), Invenergy provides this notice of an ex parte meeting with Karin Sung, Chief of Staff and Legal Advisor to Commissioner Darcie Houck and Amanda Singh, Deputy Chief of Staff and Energy Advisor to Commissioner Darcie Houck. The meeting occurred on Tuesday, March 12, 2024, from 3pm - 3:30pm via WebEx. The following non-CPUC persons in attendance were Jessica Yarnall Loarie, Invenergy; Poonum Agrawal, Invenergy; Manal Yamout McDermid, Caliber Strategies; and Shayla Funk, Caliber Strategies. During the meeting, Invenergy discussed offshore wind developments in California and general market transformation policies. Additional discussion included the importance of offshore wind in Rulemaking 20-05-003, the Integrated Resource Plan (IRP) proceeding, the IRP's role in California's transmission planning, and future regulatory processes mentioned in the Decision Adopting 2023 Preferred System Plan And Related Matters, And Addressing Two Petitions For Modification. No written materials were provided for the meeting. Respectfully submitted on March 14, 2024, in San Francisco.

303ca498d08810238cec23c2e1760614.description: NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION -LATE FILED Pursuant to Rule 8.4(a) of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission), the California Energy Storage Alliance (CESA) provides this notice of an ex parte meeting that occurred on Friday, February 9th, from 11:30 a.m. to 11:45 a.m. with Karolina Maslanka, Advisor to President Alice Reynolds and Maria Sotero, Advisor to Commissioner John Reynolds. The meeting occurred by WebEx. Rachel McMahon, Vice President, Policy for the California Energy Storage Alliance (CESA) was the sole CESA representative in the meeting. In the meeting, Rachel McMahon discussed CESAs position on two issues relevant to the pending proposed decision in R.20-05-003.  First, Ms. McMahon discussed the need for a separate proceeding track dedicated to installation of energy storage at existing natural gas plant sites.  Second, she clarified CESAs position on contracting deadlines for long duration energy storage (LDES).  No materials were provided or presented.

08c99700c3f4a8307fb0a20fec6c999c.description: CALIFORNIA WIND ENERGY ASSOCIATION NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4(a) of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission), the California Wind Energy Association (CalWEA) hereby gives notice of the following communication on February 8, 2024, from 3:00 p.m. to 3:35p.m. via WebEx audiovisual conference with CalWEA initiated by Nancy Rader, Executive Director, CalWEA, and Dariush Shirmohammadi, Technical Director, CalWEA and Karolina Maslanka, Advisor to President Alice Reynolds, and Maria Sotero, Advisor to Commissioner John Reynolds. CalWEA discussed the importance of carefully aligning the CPUCs resource portfolios with applicants in the CAISOs interconnection process to ensure that planned transmission upgrades that are intended for particular resources (in this case onshore and offshore wind) can actually be used by such resources, as discussed in CalWEAs opening and reply comments on the Preferred System Plan.  No written materials were provided.

ACP-California did not provide any written materials during the meeting.

87d8efd2b1c29dcfcf954d84464d9ddd.description: 1 BEFORE THE PUBLIC UTILITIES COMMISSIONOF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIAVINEYARD OFFSHORE, LLC THREE-DAY ADVANCED NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATIONPursuant to Rule 8.2(c)(2)(B) of the California Public Utilities Commissions (CPUC or Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, Vineyard Offshore, LLC (Vineyard Offshore) hereby gives advanced notice of the following scheduled ex parte meeting:  On December 13, 2023 at 11:00 am, the following representatives for Vineyard Offshore with meet with President Alice Reynolds energy advisor, Karolina Maslanka:  Rick Umoff (Director of Government Affairs, West Coast for Vineyard Offshore); Carrie Hitt (Senior Director, Grid and Transmission Policy for Vineyard Offshore); Randhir Singh (Director, Transmission and Interconnection for Vineyard Offshore); Maureen Gorsen (Partner at Sidley Austin LLP; and Kenneth Irvin (Partner at Sidley Austin LLP).  We understand that Maria Sotero and Caitlin Pollock from Commissioner John Reynolds office will also be present.  The meeting will take place via Webex and is expected to last thirty minutes. 955b871be31fb3e6e681c0cbc795c214.description: AMERICAN CLEAN POWER  CALIFORNIA   THREE-DAY ADVANCED NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.2(c)(2)(B) of the California Public Utilities Commissions (Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, American Clean Power  California (ACP-California) hereby gives advanced notice of the following scheduled ex parte meeting: On December 13, 2023, beginning at 4:00 p.m., Alex Jackson, Director of ACP-California, Brian Biering, Attorney for ACP-California, and Molly Croll, Director of Pacific Coast Offshore Wind for American Clean Power, will meet with Karolina Maslanka, Energy Advisor to President Reynolds.  The meeting will take place by Webex and is expected to last approximately thirty minutes. The purpose of the meeting is to discuss issues relevant to the Integrated Resource Planning proceeding, including the recent Administrative Law Judges Ruling Seeking Comment On Proposed 2023 Preferred System Plan And Transmission Planning Process Portfolios, and the Commissions forthcoming decision to provide portfolios for the 2023-2024 Transmission Planning Process.

c0087a192fa5ca60732bb4e720eec97a.description: NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION BY MICROSOFT CORPORATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4 of the California Public Utilities Commission’s (Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, Microsoft Corporation (Microsoft) hereby provides notice of oral ex parte communication in the above captioned proceedings.  This filing provides a summary of the May 2, 2023, ex parte discussion with Kerry Fleisher, Chief Advisor to President Alice Reynolds; Nick Dahlberg, Energy Advisor to President Reynolds; Suzanne Cassaza, Chief of Staff to Commissioner John Reynolds; Jake McDermott, Advisor to John Reynolds; and Caitlin Pollack, Advisor to John Reynolds.  The meeting occurred from approximately 3:30 P.M. to 4:00 P.M. via WebEx. Jonathan Noble, Senior Director of U.S. Government Affairs, Microsoft Corporation, Jordan Weiszhaar, Program Manager- Data Center Energy, Microsoft Cloud Operations and Innovation, Meredith Alexander, Consultant to Microsoft, and Carrie Bentley, Consultant to Microsoft, attended from Microsoft.   A three-day advance notice was originally only filed and served in R21-10-002, the Resource Adequacy proceeding, as the original intent was only to cover matters already in the record of that proceeding.  However, during the meeting it became clear that matters relevant to R.20-05-003, the Integrated Resources Planning proceeding, would be discussed as well in a good faith effort to comply with the Rules of Practice and Procedure, Microsoft files this report of the discussion in both dockets.

Commissioner Rechtschaffen: Sean Simon, Chief of Staff; Yulia Schmidt, Advisor; Sandy Goldberg, Advisor; Simi Rose George, Advisor; Joanna Perez-Green, Advisor; and Karin Sung, Advisor. President Reynolds: Anand Durvasula, Michael Mullaney, Interim Communications and Transportation Advisor; Jason Reiger, Interim Legal and Policy Advisor; Vanessa Baldwin, Interim Legal and Policy Advisor; Rosie O’Hara, Interim Legal; and Policy Advisor; and KerryFleisher, Interim Energy Policy Advisor. The emails are attached below as Attachment 1 and the biomass-related article as Attachment 2.
